Hysterectomy after endometrial ablation.

Unger JB(1), Meeks GR.

Author information:
(1)Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Marshfield Clinic, Wisconsin, USA.

Comment in
    Am J Obstet Gynecol. 1997 Sep;177(3):716-7.

OBJECTIVES: Our purpose was to determine the number of women undergoing 
hysterectomy after endometrial ablation and the indications for the subsequent 
surgery.
STUDY DESIGN: Forty-two premenopausal women, who had severe menorrhagia 
associated with a clinically normal examination result, underwent rollerball 
endometrial ablation between November 1990 and December 1991. Thirty-seven women 
